		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Wierd idea I have regarding mob camping...<a name="57755"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 20 04 3:28 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Create a &quot;waiting queue&quot; interface in game for single spawn point mobs such as Vindi, etc.  I think the named mobs triggered by killing place holders would be way too confusing to implement.  This idea does not apply to instanced zones obviously.
<br />

<br />
My idea comes from a couple of named I'd like to hunt fairly, but am unable to because they are perma-camped.  The peps that camp these named have the spawn times down to the second, and are unwilling to share the camp.  I don't have the time to always fight them for the camp.  Unfortunately, it is just one of the many nuances that is EQ.  I just hope this idea can remedy this somewhat.  
<br />

<br />
I was thinking that this &quot;waiting queue&quot; idea would be a fair way to solve, or at least alleviate, the perma-camp issue.  You enter the zone, pop a gui with a list of mobs, select the mob you want, and camp it.  Anyone that comes after you will be next on the list.  If you camp out, you are removed from the list.  If you kill the mob, you are removed from the list, and must re-submit.  Noone in your group or raid can be added, or add themselves individually, to the list until the mob is dead or the main person camps.  Again, just have to re-submit.  Noone else in the zone can kill the mob until it's their turn in the queue, or the queue is empty.  If you, your group, or your raid is unable to kill the mob, or just wants to give it up, you can remove yourself from the list.  At that time, anyone is able to re-submit for a chance at the mob.
<br />

<br />
This idea would at least give other characters, groups, or guilds a chance at mobs.  Your server's 6 person Gates equiped group doesn't hog old-world content that some guilds actually still persue as their main raiding focus.  For those that are farming mobs for plat, this gives a fair solution to sharing the camp.  The others behind that person can use the spawn timer (which is NOT posted) as a general way of knowing how long they have until it is their turn.  They can use that time to xp in general or do something else creatively until then.  Having a queue also means that at least 2 (or more) abled people can have the same camped item for sale on their trader.  This should help inflation and keep a healthy supply of items on hand for others to purchase.
<br />

<br />
One aspect I haven't really ironed out how this can prevent a bot army of 6 to be able to kill a mob, while not being grouped, in order for each to put his/her name on the list, thus locking the mob for themselves.  I am sure there are many other flaws with this idea.  That is why I wanted to post here.  To get your ideas, both positive and negative.  
<br />

<br />
So, what do you think?
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
