				<td colspan="2"><span>I'd rather see the market flooded than the item being uber rare because someone is hording up the mob to themselves, and twinking all their alts out bigtime, and running prices up out the butt.  I think they should go back and instance ALL old world raid zones so that each individual involved in the kill can't have access to another instance for say 7 days on a successful encounter.  And entire zones dedicated to raid type content such as ToV, Western Wastes, as well as Dragon Necropolis, Ssra, etc etc, have that zone accessible once ever 2 to 3 days.
<br />

<br />
People wouldn't need to buy crap from the bazaar if they had access to the stuff themselves instead of paying the greedy farmers, so then you wouldn't have to worry too much about market flooding.  Most of the stuff you'd be flooding the market with is stuff not many people really care about anyway.</span></td>
